{"name": "langgraph-checkpoint-cosmosdb", "metadata": {"name": "langgraph-checkpoint-cosmosdb", "version": "0.2.1", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["azure-cosmos", "langchain-core", "langgraph"], "summary": "Azure CosmosDB checkpoint saver implementation for LangGraph", "upload_time": 1734853118}, "documentation": ["# LangGraph DynamoDB Saver\n\nA DynamoDB-based checkpoint saver implementation for LangGraph applications.\n\n## Installation\n\nbash\npip install langgraph-dynamodb-saver\n\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- AWS credentials configured (either through environment variables, AWS CLI, or IAM roles)\n- Appropriate permissions to create and access DynamoDB tables\n\n## Usage\n\npython\nfrom langgraph_dynamodb_saver import DynamoDBSaver\n\n# Create a new saver instance with a table name\nsaver = DynamoDBSaver(table_name=\"my-checkpoints\")\n\n# Using context manager\nwith DynamoDBSaver.from_conn_info(table_name=\"my-checkpoints\") as saver:\n    # Use the saver in your LangGraph application\n    pass\n\n\n## Configuration\n\nThe DynamoDB saver automatically creates a table if it doesn't exist with the following structure:\n\n- Partition Key (PK): String\n- Sort Key (SK): String\n- On-demand billing mode\n- Default throughput limits:\n  - Max Read Request Units: 100\n  - Max Write Request Units: 100\n\n## Environment Variables\n\nEnsure your AWS credentials are properly configured using one of these methods:\n\nbash\n# Option 1: Environment variables\nexport AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=\"your_access_key\"\nexport AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=\"your_secret_key\"\nexport AWS_REGION=\"your_region\"\n\n## Error Handling\n\nThe saver will:\n- Automatically create the DynamoDB table if it doesn't exist\n- Handle connection and operation retries\n- Raise appropriate exceptions for permission issues or AWS service problems\n\n## Limitations\n\n- DynamoDB item size limit of 400KB applies to individual checkpoints\n- Queries are eventually consistent by default\n- Table names must be unique within an AWS region\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "langgraph_checkpoint_cosmosdb", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "langgraph_checkpoint_cosmosdb.CosmosDBSaver", "xref": {"fqname": "langgraph_checkpoint_cosmosdb.cosmosdbSaver.CosmosDBSaver", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "langgraph_checkpoint_cosmosdb.cosmosSerializer", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "langgraph_checkpoint_cosmosdb.cosmosSerializer.CosmosSerializer", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "langgraph_checkpoint_cosmosdb.cosmosSerializer.CosmosSerializer.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "serde", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "langgraph_checkpoint_cosmosdb.cosmosSerializer.CosmosSerializer.dumps_typed", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "obj", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "langgraph_checkpoint_cosmosdb.cosmosSerializer.CosmosSerializer.loads_typed", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "data", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "langgraph_checkpoint_cosmosdb.cosmosSerializer.CosmosSerializer.dumps", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "obj", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "langgraph_checkpoint_cosmosdb.cosmosSerializer.CosmosSerializer.loads", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "serialized_obj", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "